The paper proposes a method for feature selection and data reconstruction using neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning. Specifically, the method involves using a concrete selector layer as the encoder and a standard neural network as the decoder, which suggests that it is related to deep learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CL (Computation and Language), as these sub-categories are all related to machine learning and deep learning.
